result.notes:
The figures presented here provide information about the National Curriculum Key Stage 3 (KS3) test results for pupils in maintained schools in England. The results refer to the achievements of KS3 eligible pupils in the English, Mathematics and Science core subjects. These are typically 14-year-old pupils; however the tests may have been taken by a minority of slightly older and younger pupils.  A breakdown by pupil Free School Meal (FSM) eligibility is also included.

Source: Department for Children Schools and Families (DCSF)

Publisher: Neighbourhood Statistics

Geographies: Middle Layer Super Output Area (MSOA), Local Authority District (LAD), Government Office Region (GOR), National

Geographic coverage: England

Time coverage: 2004/05 to 2006/07

Type of data: Administrative data
